== Wedges ==

Preheat your oven to 200°C and remove the @unsalted butter{30%g} and @21 day aged British sirloin steaks{2} from the fridge to bring them up to room temperature.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @olive oil{1%tbsp}, then season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

== Sundried Tomato Butter ==

Meanwhile, put the @butter{} with half the @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g} into a #small bowl{} and mash together with a #fork{} until well combined.

== Dressing and Salad ==

In a #medium bowl{}, mix the remaining sundried tomato paste with the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} and @olive oil{} (see ingredients for amount). Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} and set aside.

Slice the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} in half and pop in the bowl with the dressing. Mix together.

== Steak ==

About ~{8-10%minutes} before the potatoes are done, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. Season the steaks with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. When the oil is hot, lay the steaks in the pan and brown for ~{1%minute} on each side.

Lower the heat slightly and cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side for medium rare.

> Cook for 1-2 mins more if you like it more cooked. The steak is safe to eat when the outside is cooked.

Once cooked, smother the steaks with the butter so it melts nicely in the pan, ~{1%minute}. Remove from the pan to a #plate{} and let the steak rest for ~{2-3%minutes} while you plate up (don't discard the butter in the pan!).

Add the @wild rocket{40%g} to the tomatoes and dressing, toss to coat.

Divide the potato wedges and salad among the plates. Slice the steak on a #board{} into thin strips and add to the plate with the remaining buttery juices from the pan and plate drizzled over the top. Enjoy!